      • fixExpression

        public static java.lang.String fixExpression(java.lang.String pEq)
        Fixes any terms that might be misleading to the compiler. For example, sinx will become sin(x). Note: To not have it do any fixing, put a "@" at the beginning of the input String
        Parameters:
        pEq - The expression to be corrected.
        Returns:
        A corrected version of the expression.

      • parseTokens

        public static java.util.ArrayList<Token> parseTokens(java.lang.String rEq)
                                              throws TypeMisMatchException
        Generates an ArrayList of tokens that represent rEq. Note that this removes all whitespace (including spaces) before handling the expression.
        Parameters:
        rEq - The expression to be parsed.
        Returns:
        An ArrayList of tokens, each representing a different chunk of the expression.
        Throws:
        TypeMisMatchException
        See Also:
        Token
